src:
Big sports events today
04 Nov 2019, 18:45 by TIMESOFINDIA.COM
NEW DELHI: Here are the big sports events lined up for Tuesday (November 5) that comprise the action from China Open badminton tournament.

(All timings in IST)


6:30 am (Cricket - 3rd T20I)


New Zealand vs England


7:30 am (Badminton - China Open)

Satwiksairaj Rankireddy/Ashwini Ponnappa vs Joshua Hurlburt-Yu/Josephine Wu (Canada) in mixed doubles first round (Satwiksairaj Rankireddy/Ashwini Ponnappa won 21-19, 21-19)

7:40 am (Badminton - China Open)

Rasmus Gemke (Denmark) vs HS Prannoy in men's singles first round (HS Prannoy lost 17-21, 18-21)

9:10 am (Badminton - China Open)

PV Sindhu vs Pai Yu Po (Chinese Taipei) in women's singles first round

11:00 am approx (Badminton - China Open)

Li Wen Mei/Zheng Yu (China) vs Ashwini Ponnappa/N Sikki Reddy in women's doubles first round

1:40 pm (Cricket - 2nd T20I)


Australia vs Pakistan


2:00 pm approx (Badminton - China Open)

Phillip Chew/Ryan Chew (USA) vs Satwiksairaj Rankireddy/Chirag Shetty in men's doubles first round

11:25 pm (Football - UEFA Champions League)

Barcelona vs Slavia Praha
Zenit vs RB Leipzig
